HEADWORD: Roulade
<hw>Rou`lade"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A smoothly running passage of short notes (as
semiquavers, or sixteenths) uniformly grouped, sung upon one long
syllable, as in Handel's oratorios.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

